text: Polina Yuryevna Mikhaylova (; born 31 August 1986) is a Russian table tennis player. She competed at the 2016 Summer Olympics in the women's singles event, in which she was eliminated in the second round by Viktoria Pavlovich. ==References== Category:1986 births Category:Living people Category:Russian female table tennis players Category:Olympic table tennis players of Russia Category:Table tennis players at the 2016 Summer Olympics Category:Universiade medalists in table tennis Category:Universiade silver medalists for Russia Category:European Games competitors for Russia Category:Table tennis players at the 2015 European Games Category:Table tennis players at the 2019 European Games
title: Polina Mikhaylova
